news.title: Delhi civic body starts drive over property tax dues
news.para: MCD targets to collect Rs 3,850 crore in property tax in the financial year 2022-23 and only Rs 1,671 crore has been collected. Last year, it collected around Rs 2,000 crore.

news.title: Debenture holders reach deal, withdraw insolvency plea against Peninsula Land
news.para: They claimed that Peninsula Land, the holding company, had guaranteed the debentures issued by the step down subsidiary. ICICI Prudential Real Estate AIF is the debenture holder. There are no debenture holders from the general public.

news.title: Delhi HC sets aside arbitrator order against Indiabulls Housing in Shipra Mall dispute
news.para: The arbitrator had set aside Indiabulls' four sale notices issued under the SARFAESI Act and Security Interest (Enforcement) Rules, 2002 in June last year after Shipra Estate, Shipra Hotels, and Shipra Leasing approached it, seeking to maintain status quo in relation to the securities provided by them against loan availed from the non-banking finance company.

news.title: Gujarat RERA posts vacant, 150 projects in limbo
news.para: Real estate developers are demanding that the state government appoint the RERA chairman and two members, even on an in-charge basis, so that regular functioning of the authority can continue.

news.title: ASK Finance closes Rs 40 crore debt transaction with Sowparnika Projects & Infrastructure
news.para: The investment has been made in Sowparnika Ashiyana, a mid-income affordable project near Whitefield, Bangalore, with over 750 homes. According to the sources the raised capital will be used for the construction and give exit to Edelweiss.

news.title: M3M secures Rs 1,500 crore from PAG Credit & Markets
news.para: "As per the deal, the money will come in four tranches of Rs 600 crore, Rs 300 crore, Rs 250 crore and Rs 350 crore and be paid back within 18 months," said one of the people cited earlier. “The company is also eyeing more acquisitions, so money will be used for expansion too.”

news.title: Kolkata development body starts razing drive to reclaim plots off Bypass
news.para: The KMDA on Monday pulled down unauthorized structures, one of them a three-storey building, on two plots close to the Gitanjali stadium in Kasba. Once the razing is finished, the land will be fenced off and the authorities will auction them.

news.title: Six illegal borewells sealed in four highrises of Greater Noida, builders to be fined
news.para: Two borewells have been sealed in Ajnara Le Garden Society, two in Eco Village 3, and one each in Ajnara Homes and JNC The Park societies. Along with the sealing of the borewells, the builders of the four housing societies will also be fined, officials said.

news.title: Make digital connectivity infra mandatory in building plans: Trai to Government
news.para: ​The telecom sector regulator suggested creating provisions under the real estate law RERA for mandating digital connectivity infrastructure inside the buildings, its maintenance and timely upgradation.

news.title: Nagpur civic body proposes hike in property, other taxes
news.para: “If okayed by administrator and municipal commissioner Radhakrishnan B, citizens will have to shell out higher NMC tax from 2023-24,” said a source.

news.title: Hyderabad development body's lottery for Rajiv Swagruha flats on March 3
news.para: There are more than 1,000 flats including 3-BHK, 2-BHK and 1-BHK which were unsold in the previous bids. Officials said those who can pay the token advance of ₹3 lakh, ₹2 lakh and ₹1 lakh for 3-BHK, 2-BHK and 1-BHK flats before February 15 are eligible for the lottery.

news.title: Bhopal civic body's affordable housing units could be disposed off under PMAY
news.para: BMC will appoint RERA-approved marketing agency or personnel for sale of unsold units,” said BMC additional commissioner, Chandra Pratap Gohal.

news.title: Bombay HC rejects PIL against additional FSI given to Pila House redevelopment
news.para: The PIL claimed that then BMC chief Iqbal Chahal had in November 2020 and August 2021, “illegally’’ given the builder, Rubberwala Housing and Infrastructure over 20,000 sq ft more than permissible developable space for redevelopment of Pila House-platinum in the Grant Road area.

news.title: Wife co-owner? Pay tax on 50% property income
news.para: Ruling in the case of Shivani Madan (the taxpayer), the ITAT consequently upheld a taxation of Rs 9.8 lakh in her hands during the financial year 2014-15 (the year pertaining to the litigation).

news.title: Five months on, only 12% Gurugram societies opted for unified billing system
news.para: DHBVN rolled out the unified billing system in September last year after receiving repeated complaints from residents that bills raised by the builder or RWAs are not following the standard tariff of DHBVN, as a result of which they aren't able to get the benefit of differential slab tariff.
